    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You users should have their own keys and not use one centrally managed by you. If you are using central keys, it's up to you to publish transactions with high enough fees to get them included. AFAIK Geth's suggested gas price will always get you into the next 1-2 blocks. Not really clear if you set that yourself ot whether you let Geth suggest one.\r\n\r\n> It works like prehistoric single-threaded application.\r\n\r\nWell, yes, if you use one key, it's one thread. That's kind of the point of not having a single key, rather letting your users use their own keys (+ security).\r\n\r\n> But nobody knows how to do it.\r\n\r\nYou not knowing is not \"nobody knows\". Tracking nonces / transactions yourself means that if you have a lot of tx traffic to do, it makes sense to not just fire to Geth and forget, rather to tell Geth \"publish this tx with nonce 5\". And then if it doesn't get included fast enough for your use case, you can always republish a new tx with nonce 5.\r\n\r\n> You have developed piece of junk!\r\n\r\n$250B piece of junk FTW ",
